com.nokia.places

Interface ResultPage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Page

    public interface ResultPage
extends Page
    This interface represents the basis of a paginated collection.
    See Also:
    Nokia's Restful Places API - paginated collections

    • Method Detail

      • getItems

        PlaceLink[] getItems()
        This method retrieves a list containing the objects of the current page of the collection, including items, editorials, images, and reviews. The type of the objects in the list depends on the collection.

        Note: If a collection is empty, the items attribute is not present.

        Returns:
        The list containing the collection items, or null if the collection is empty.

      • getItem

        PlaceLink getItem(int index)
        This method retrieves a specified PlaceLink items from the result set.
        Parameters:
        index - the index of the item to retrieve.
        Returns:
        A PlaceLink with a summary of the place.

      • getNumberOfItems

        int getNumberOfItems()
        This method retrieves the number of PlaceLink items which can be obtained from this result page.
        Returns:
        The number of available PlaceLink items.

      • getTotalAvailableItemCount

        java.lang.Integer getTotalAvailableItemCount()
        This method retrieves the total number of items available for a place. For example, if a result has 50 places and no other items, the return value of a call to this method would be 50.

        Note: It is not always possible to calculate the total number of elements in a collection. The attribute, therefore, might be missing, or might contain just an estimate. Instead of relying on the presence of the attribute, clients must rely on the existence of the next attribute to find out if additional items are available.

        Specified by:
        getTotalAvailableItemCount in interface Page
        Returns:
        The total number of available items (could be null).

      • getOffsetCount

        java.lang.Integer getOffsetCount()
        This method retrieves the index number of the first item in the current page.

        Pages other than the first page of a collection may include the attribute that this method gets, which contains the index of the first item in the current page.

        Specified by:
        getOffsetCount in interface Page
        Returns:
        The index number of the first item in the current page for the entire collection (could be null).

      • nextPage

        ResultPage nextPage()
                    throws java.io.IOException,
                           ServiceError
        This method makes a request to retrieve the next result page of n place links from the Restful Places service. The call to RESTful Places service is made synchronously, and therefore blocks further operations until the request is complete.
        Returns:
        A paginated collection of PlaceLink objects.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - IOException on I/O errors
        ServiceError - on service errors

      • nextPage

        void nextPage(ResultPageRequestListener listener)
        This method makes a request to retrieve the next result page of n place links from the Restful Places service. The call to RESTful Places service is made asynchronously. It is not blocking.
        Parameters:
        listener - pair of callback functions, one of which shall be called once the request has completed. The listener contains either the result of the request or the error should one occur.

      • getSearchContext

        SearchContext getSearchContext()
        Details about the location the search was centred upon.
        Returns:
        The context of the search
